cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.PF, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with load balancing of tasks on servers, which is a problem in computer networks and distributed systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networks and Internet Architecture) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of algorithms for load balancing, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.PF (Performance). Finally, the paper uses an exploration-exploitation approach, which is a common technique in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
